The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, July 19, 2004  LOOSE CHANGE
																								Aviva Life Insurance has unveiled the LoanShield scheme, a group insurance plan for CanFin housing loan customers. The policy will cover the home loan obligation of the insured member against death and permanent disability during the term of the policy. In the event of any unfortunate incident, the insurance company will pay off the outstanding loan amount.																								Standard Chartered Mutual Fund has launched its third floating rate fund  Grindlays Floating Rate-Long Term Plan. It will have two sub-plans  Plan A (regular plan) and Plan B (institutional plan). The issue is open till July 30. The minimum application amounts for Plan A and Plan B are Rs 500 and Rs 1 crore, respectively. For Plan A, there is an exit load of 0.5 per cent up to an investment of Rs 10 lakh, if redeemed within six months and no exit load for Plan B. 																								Birla Mutual Fund will launch Quarterly Series-1 in its fixed maturity plan. The minimum application amount will be Rs 5,000. There will be an exit load of 2 per cent if the units are redeemed before the due date. The scheme will remain open between July 22 and August 2. The fund has revised the entry load of Birla Equity Plan. The scheme will now charge an entry load of 2.25 per cent on investments less than Rs 5 crore.
